                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5294: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the American Delegation to the Sixth International Conference of
                        American States</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hughes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-23T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. For Mr. Francis White. The following is the text of the substitute project
                    approved by the Chamber of Deputies as telegraphed by Munro:</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text quoted in paragraph 2 of telegram No. 36, January 20, 9
                    a.m., from the Chargé in Nicaragua, printed on <ref target="#pg_440">page
                        440</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
